The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, June 07, 2004 				 United Phosphorus to raise foreign loans
																								Calcutta, June 6 (PTI): United Phosphorus Limited is planning to raise $100 million through international offering to retire high-cost debts, meet normal capital expenditure and invest in overseas ventures.																								Officials said the timing of the issue has not yet been decided. The proceeds would also be utilised for redemption of redeemable preference shares, funding long-term working capital requirements and setting up marketing and distribution offices abroad, they added.																								The detailed terms and conditions for the offer will be determined in consultation with advisers, lead managers, underwriters and such other authority, they said.																								As a prelude to the issue, an enabling resolution seeking permission of shareholders for raising the fund would be placed during an extra-ordinary general meeting of the Gujarat-headquartered company on June 21.																								Securities issued pursuant to the international offer would be listed either or at all the stock exchanges of Luxembourg, London and Singapore, the officials added. 
